Job Description
       Job Title: Multi-Skilled Maintenance Engineer
       Reference: 6857640
       Venn Group has been approached by an established contractor to recruit a Multi-Skilled Maintenance Engineer on a on a permanent basis.
       As the successful candidate you will have previous experience in Electrical and mechanical maintenance support to sites as part of a Maintenance team.
       The duties will include:
       * Respond to breakdowns across three sites
       * Repair, modify and improve all areas of plant within the group
       * Carry out plant improvement projects
       * Assist with maintenance of the plant as required
       * Apply the highest standards of health and safety during all tasks, as per company procedures
       * Be a proactive member of any continuous improvement initiatives
       * To be proactive on each site and identify work that needs to be carried out
       * Work with other members of the Maintenance team and all employees on site to ensure smooth running of the plant
       Essential Skills/Qualifications:
       * Relevant electrical and mechanical qualifications preferably time served
       * Electrically biased with a firm knowledge of mechanical maintenance preferred
       * Minimum of 2 years' experience
       * Recycling/Process/Quarry industry experience desirable
       * Experienced in production environments
       * Working knowledge of conveyor, bearings, gearboxes and motors required
       * Basic knowledge of Siemens S7 (fault finding) desirable
       * Familiar with 110/240/415V and control circuits
       * Must be able to read electrical drawings
       * Basic electrical fault finding and disconnect/reconnect required
       * Full driving license / own transport essential
       * Ability to organise, plan and procure materials for medium sized repair or upgrade works
       * Positive, can do attitude and self-motivated
       * Well organised and works well under pressure
       * IT literacy and advantage
       * Excellent interpersonal skills
       To discuss this position in more detail or to apply please send an up to date CV to northeng@venngroup.com or call Sam Cornwell or Joe Williams on 0161 830 1830.
       Venn Group is an equal opportunities employment business and employment agency and welcomes applications from all candidates.</Value></Field>
